HEADWORD: Impressionism
<hw>Im*pres"sion*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>impressionnisme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>The
theory or method of suggesting an effect or impression without
elaboration of the details; -- a designation of a recent fashion in
painting and etching.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impressionist</ent>⟦br⟧
